# Image uploads — Cloudflare R2 (S3-compatible). When ALL of these are set, the API server
# (server/upload.ts) stores uploaded images in R2 and saves their public URL on the component.
# When unset, it falls back to writing files under public/uploads/ (dev only) — no config needed.
#
# Copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in. To get these:
#   1. Create an R2 bucket in the Cloudflare dashboard.
#   2. Enable public access (r2.dev) or attach a custom domain — that URL is R2_PUBLIC_BASE_URL.
#   3. Create an R2 API token (S3 Auth) → gives the Access Key ID + Secret Access Key.
#   4. Account ID is shown on the R2 overview page.

R2_ACCOUNT_ID=
R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
R2_BUCKET=
# Public base URL for the bucket (no trailing slash), e.g.
#   https://pub-xxxxxxxx.r2.dev   or   https://assets.yourdomain.com
R2_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=

# The `dev:api` / `dev` scripts load this file automatically (tsx --env-file-if-exists=.env),
# so just create .env and restart the API server. In production, set these as real env vars.
